An AI assistant product line based on large language models. Every valid configuration must include a Model, a Plan, and an Access option. A configuration can optionally include FineTuning, Temperature, ImageGeneration, and WebSearch. Exactly one Model must be selected among GPT4o, Gemini, or Claude, each one providing different cost and context window size (tokens) represented by attributes: GPT4o (cost 8, 128k tokens), Gemini (cost 10, 1M tokens), and Claude (cost 9, 200k tokens). Similarly, exactly one subscription plan must be chosen between Free and Premium, allowing up to 50 and 1000 queries per month, respectively. The assistant must include at least one access mechanism: WebApp, API, or both. The API option introduces an additional cost of 2. Optional features extend the assistant's capabilities. FineTuning enables advanced customization at an extra cost of 5, while Temperature controls response variability and is defined as an integer parameter ranging from 0 to 5. Additionally, ImageGeneration and WebSearch provide complementary functionalities. Several cross-tree constraints restrict valid configurations. Image generation is only supported when using GPT4o or Gemini. The API option cannot be combined with WebSearch. Moreover, FineTuning is available if and only if the Premium plan is selected. Finally, features are enriched with attributes such as numerical values (cost, monthLimit) and string values to model context size (tokens). The overall sum of the costs of the selected features must remain below 15.